National Security Advisor General James Jones visited New Delhi at the invitation of his Indian counterpart, Shivshankar Menon. During his visit, General Jones met with NSA Menon and other senior Indian officials to discuss various bilateral issues, including regional security, cooperation in Afghanistan, and trade and economic relations. General Jones also discussed preparations for President Obama's upcoming visit later in the year and expressed his hope that it would demonstrate the strong cooperation and enduring partnership between the United States and India. The visit served to strengthen the strategic partnership between the two countries and identify areas for further mutual cooperation. General Jones also met with Prime Minister Singh, Minister for Home Affairs Chidambaram, Minister for Defense Antony, Chairman of Chiefs of Staff Committee Naik, and Leader of the Opposition Jaitley, expressing appreciation for their hospitality and warmth.